From e2b9310129957038b40bcb1e5e92843c6c3041c6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andre Mauricio Zelak <andre.zelak@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 19:40:39 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 03/11] Best source selection algorithm

An algorithm to select the best available clock and use it
as clock source.

A new set of configuration options was introduced to control
the clock requirements. The clock which fails to match the
requirements is discarded.

The new configuration options are:
* ha_max_local_clockClass
* ha_max_local_clockAccuracy
* ha_max_local_offsetScaledLogVar
* ha_max_gm_clockClass
* ha_max_gm_clockAccuracy
* ha_max_gm_offsetScaledLogVar
* ha_gm_timeTraceable
* ha_gm_frequencyTraceable

The local and Grandmaster options define the maximum value
it's acceptable, including the value itsef, ie. a source
clock which local clock class value is lower or equal to
ha_max_local_clockClass is considered a valid source.

The time and frequency traceable options when set enable
the flag verification, ie. when ha_gm_timeTraceable a
source clock is valid only if its time traceable flag
is set.

If a single clock matches the requirements, it is selected
as source.

If one or more clock match requirements, the clock with the highest
priority is selected. In case of tie, the 1st configured clock is
selected.

The ha_priority option is an interface setting used to configure
the clock priority. The lowest priority is 0 and the highest is 254,
and the default value is 0. The ha_priority is used as a tie breaker
when more then one source clock matches the requirements.

And if no clock match requirements, the clock with the best local
clock class is selected.

Test Plan:
PASS In a system configure as PTP T-BC with two external GMs, source
     clocks configured with the same priority.

     system ptp-instance-parameter-add phc-instc01 cmdline_opts='-w'
         ha_enabled=1
     system ptp-interface-add phc-iface01 phc-instc01
     system host-if-ptp-assign controller-0 enp81s0f3 phc-iface01
     system ptp-interface-parameter-add phc-iface01 ha_domainNumber=24
         ha_uds_address=/var/run/ptp4l-ptpinstc01
     system ptp-interface-add phc-iface02 phc-instc01
     system host-if-ptp-assign controller-0 enp138s0f3 phc-iface01
     system ptp-interface-parameter-add phc-iface02 ha_domainNumber=25
         ha_uds_address=/var/run/ptp4l-ptpinstc02

     When both GMs are available and valid
     Then enp81s0f3 is selected as source, because it was the first
     source configured.
     When GM connected to enp81s0f3 degrades
     Then the enp138s0f3 is selected as source, as the only one valid.
     When GM connected to enp81s0f3 recovers
     Then the enp138s0f3 remains the selected source. As both sources
     have the same priority, the one already selected remains the
     source.

PASS In a system configure as PTP T-BC with two external GMs, source
     clocks configured with the different priorities.

     system ptp-interface-parameter-add phc-iface01 ha_priority=200
     system ptp-interface-parameter-add phc-iface02 ha_priority=210

     When both GMs are available and valid
     Then enp138s0f3 is selected as source, beucase it has the highest
     priority.
     When the GM connected to enp138s0f3 degrades
     Then enp81s0f3 is selected as source
     When the GM connected to enp138s0f3 recovers
     Then enp138s0f3 is selected as source (non stability timer scenario)

     The stability timer was not delivered in this change.

Signed-off-by: Andre Mauricio Zelak <andre.zelak@windriver.com>
